1
00:00:19,240 --> 00:00:22,198
[THE SEEKERS' "GEORGY GIRL"
PLAYS]

2
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:04,434
[PIANO PLAYING]

3
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:08,673
One and two, and one and two.
One and two, and one and two.

4
00:03:08,880 --> 00:03:10,791
Everybody go around.

5
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:17,152
Very good. Faster.

6
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:23,677
One and two.
One and two, and one and two.

7
00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:26,878
One and two, and one and two.
Very good.

8
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:30,032
All right, everybody around me.
Come on. Quick. Quick, quick.

9
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:33,038
One more quickly, to finish.
You're all things in space.

10
00:03:33,240 --> 00:03:34,673
[ELECTRONIC MUSIC PLAYS
ON REEL-TO-REEL]

11
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:36,154
All right. Spin into a space.

12
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:39,636
And one, two, three.
On the floor. Quick.

13
00:04:20,960 --> 00:04:22,837
She's looking better.

14
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:24,992
She ought to be under the doctor.

15
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:27,111
Let's hope that's the end
of the cats' chorus.

16
00:04:27,320 --> 00:04:31,393
She don't believe in doctors.
You can't call it anything else.

17
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:32,874
Certainly not music.

18
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:35,554
CHILDREN: Bye.
GEORGY: Bye. Bye!

19
00:04:35,840 --> 00:04:39,879
Ah. I'll catch her before she goes
back to the slums.

20
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:42,511
[HUMMING AND WHISTLING]

21
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:18,868
I've got a bone to pick with you.
Working, Father dear.

22
00:05:19,080 --> 00:05:20,798
What do you think this is?

23
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:25,233
It's a dress for you. A present.

24
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:27,112
From my other daddy?
The rich one?

25
00:05:30,160 --> 00:05:31,275
Oh.

26
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:34,912
Oh, that's gorgeous.
That's the height of chic.

27
00:05:35,160 --> 00:05:36,718
Oh, have you tried it on?

28
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:38,990
You'll feel the back of my hand
in a minute.

29
00:05:46,120 --> 00:05:48,588
It's to wear to his birthday party
on Thursday.

30
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:52,315
The one to which you were invited.
I posted the card myself.

31
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:55,718
Now, I had no education
of which to speak.

32
00:05:55,920 --> 00:05:59,799
I didn't get sent
to a finishing school in Switzerland
by my father's employer.

33
00:06:00,440 --> 00:06:02,431
I went to an elementary school.

34
00:06:02,960 --> 00:06:05,520
But what education I got,
I got from him!

35
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:08,757
Like knowing what RSVP means.
I'm not coming.

36
00:06:08,960 --> 00:06:10,916
You'll be there.
I shan't.

37
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:14,271
If I have anything to do with it.
You haven't.

38
00:06:14,520 --> 00:06:15,919
Oh, please yourself.

39
00:06:17,080 --> 00:06:18,752
It's up to you.
Go and live in that slum

40
00:06:18,960 --> 00:06:20,234
instead of here.
Thanks.

41
00:06:20,440 --> 00:06:23,113
But for his sake,
you ought to try and do
something about yourself.

42
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:26,869
You walk about
looking like a bloody tramp.

43
00:06:27,080 --> 00:06:29,116
Why don't you get your hair done?

44
00:06:29,320 --> 00:06:31,754
I have just had it done.

45
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:33,473
[CAR HONKING]

46
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:36,992
GEORGY:
Run, then.

47
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:40,237
[GEORGY PLAYING PIANO]

48
00:07:06,720 --> 00:07:08,438
I've got the tickets.

49
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:13,513
Tickets?

50
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:16,353
TED:
The Cup Final tickets.

51
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:19,558
Who said anything about tickets
to the Cup Final?

52
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:21,478
You did, Mr James.
Oh?

53
00:07:22,520 --> 00:07:26,149
You did, really.
You said I should go with you.

54
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:28,954
Is that so? Well, well.

55
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:32,909
They cost me two £5 notes.
Two £5 notes?

56
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:38,197
Georgy's not gone yet.
I wanted to catch her.

57
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:41,437
[ELECTRONIC MUSIC PLAYS
ON REEL-TO-REEL]

58
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:57,438
The bedroom.

59
00:08:02,440 --> 00:08:03,668
Georgy?

60
00:08:11,960 --> 00:08:13,234
She's nipped off.

61
00:08:13,440 --> 00:08:17,274
By the look of it. If I were you, Ted,
I'd take her across my knee,

62
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:20,517
pull down her knickers
and give her a good tanning.

63
00:08:20,720 --> 00:08:24,269
Oh. She's too big for that.
Yes. She always was.

64
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:28,792
She's like some enormous
lorry driver.

65
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:32,193
She ought to be made to feel
what she owes me.

66
00:08:32,400 --> 00:08:36,029
Oh, I rub that in,
don't you worry, sir.
I hold the whip hand.

67
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:40,109
<i>TED [ON TAPE]: I've got a bone to pick. 
GEORGY: Working, Father dear. </i>

68
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:41,833
<i>TED:
What do you think this is? </i>

69
00:08:42,040 --> 00:08:44,315
<i>It's a dress for you. A present. </i>

70
00:08:44,520 --> 00:08:46,590
<i>GEORGY: From my other daddy? 
The rich one? </i>

71
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:49,189
<i>TED: Oh, that's gorgeous. 
That's the height of chic. </i>

72
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:51,510
<i>GEORGY:
Oh, have you tried it on? </i>

73
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:53,711
<i>TED: You'll feel the back
of my hand in a minute.</i>

74
00:08:53,920 --> 00:08:55,911
[LAUGHING]

75
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:00,955
ELLEN:
Oh, James, you got the things?

76
00:09:08,760 --> 00:09:11,513
How are you feeling?
Horrible.

77
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:14,154
You know, Ellen,
when you're not feeling well,

78
00:09:14,360 --> 00:09:16,316
you ought to see a proper doctor.

79
00:09:16,520 --> 00:09:18,158
Doctors.

80
00:09:18,680 --> 00:09:20,875
You got the yeast compound?

81
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:24,400
Yeast compound.
The wintergreen?

82
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:27,508
Wintergreen.

83
00:09:27,720 --> 00:09:29,438
Cider vinegar?

84
00:09:29,640 --> 00:09:33,633
Well, they hadn't got the brand
that you wanted.

85
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:35,159
Oh.

86
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:39,070
[***]

87
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:53,473
GEORGY: Hello.
BO Y: Georgy, come and play with us.

88
00:09:53,680 --> 00:09:55,398
GEORGY:
Come on.

89
00:09:56,320 --> 00:09:58,117
BO Y:
Ah, come on, Georgy.

90
00:10:00,560 --> 00:10:02,312
GEORGY:
Everybody up.

91
00:10:05,640 --> 00:10:07,551
BO Y: Bye.
Bye.

92
00:10:22,760 --> 00:10:25,149
Hi.
Hi.

93
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,911
Has it been raining?
Oh, the baths.

94
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:29,838
I'm training to be
an Olympic swimmer.

95
00:10:30,040 --> 00:10:31,871
This man came up to me
in the street, a Scotsman...

96
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:34,036
Shut up, Georgy.
Am I all right?

97
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:36,276
Sensational.
Am I all right?

98
00:10:36,480 --> 00:10:37,674
Sensational.

99
00:10:37,880 --> 00:10:38,869
[CAR HONKING]

100
00:10:39,080 --> 00:10:40,433
Where are you going?
Out.

101
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:43,757
But Jos. Isn't Jos coming?
Of course.

102
00:10:43,960 --> 00:10:45,871
You can't go out!

103
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:47,798
Can't I? Bye.

104
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,513
Hey!

105
00:10:54,240 --> 00:10:57,676
Meredith! Take your fiddle.
For God's sake, what for?

106
00:10:57,880 --> 00:10:59,598
You can tell Jos
you're rehearsing.

107
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:03,076
Why?
Well, you know. What will I tell him?

108
00:11:03,280 --> 00:11:05,748
That I'm out. That's all.
I'll be back at 8.

109
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,797
But what will I say? What will I do?

110
00:11:08,560 --> 00:11:10,312
Keep him happy.

111
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:19,239
[***]

112
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:44,911
[DOORBELL RINGING]

113
00:11:54,360 --> 00:11:57,397
You naked underneath that coat?
Stark.

114
00:11:57,720 --> 00:11:59,392
Let's have a look, then.

115
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:02,831
It's threepence.
Too dear, dear.

116
00:12:03,680 --> 00:12:07,389
Where's that rude girl, huh?
Lying lasciviously in bed?

117
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:10,911
Contemplating in the loo?

118
00:12:12,640 --> 00:12:16,394
Aha. Lounging in the bath.

119
00:12:17,360 --> 00:12:19,715
* You look a little lovelier each day **

120
00:12:19,920 --> 00:12:21,911
She's gone out, Jos.

121
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:24,678
She had to.

122
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:26,838
Suddenly.
Uh-huh.

123
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:30,875
I bought some supper
for the two of us.

124
00:12:33,440 --> 00:12:36,000
Soggy.
I meant Meredith and me.

125
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:38,634
Obviously.
Now she's out.

126
00:12:39,280 --> 00:12:42,078
She say any time?
Eight... 7.30.

127
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:48,397
Get out the Scrabble, then.

128
00:12:51,640 --> 00:12:54,791
Hungry?
Starving.

129
00:13:09,360 --> 00:13:12,716
Oh...

130
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:16,033
It ain't no good, you bawling.

131
00:13:19,680 --> 00:13:23,036
He was a good man, mister.
I made mincemeat out of him.

132
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:24,912
He always loved his mince.

133
00:13:25,840 --> 00:13:28,991
Quit stalling. I'll pump you
full of lead. You're a
two-timing broad.

134
00:13:29,200 --> 00:13:31,350
No, not broad.
Yes. Very long.

135
00:13:31,560 --> 00:13:34,677
Very long, but you're a broad too.
Are you longer than you are broad?

136
00:13:34,880 --> 00:13:36,359
Or broader than your long?

137
00:13:36,560 --> 00:13:39,313
How is your broader anyway,
and your sister?

138
00:13:44,480 --> 00:13:46,710
[MUSIC PLAYS ON RADIO]

139
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:52,236
<i>MAN [ON RADIO]: A look at
our programmes later this evening. </i>

140
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:56,479
<i>At half past seven,  You're a Brick, 
a brand-new radio panel game</i>

141
00:13:56,680 --> 00:13:59,148
<i>with the accent on the building trade.
Then at 8:00... </i>

142
00:13:59,360 --> 00:14:03,638
[MUSIC PLAYS ON RADIO]

143
00:14:18,880 --> 00:14:21,474
O-C-H-R-E. Ochre. I win.

144
00:14:21,680 --> 00:14:23,910
I had zho. Z-H-O.

145
00:14:24,120 --> 00:14:26,714
What's that when it's at home?
A Himalayan ox.

146
00:14:26,920 --> 00:14:28,319
Truly?
Truly.

147
00:14:28,520 --> 00:14:31,637
We had some good words:
catagmatic, sostenuto.

148
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:34,479
One of the few advantages
of a musical education, my dear.

149
00:14:34,680 --> 00:14:35,795
[WHISTLING]

150
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:37,433
You ought to leave that bank, Jos.

151
00:14:37,640 --> 00:14:39,835
Go back to your proper work.
I wish I could, George.

152
00:14:40,040 --> 00:14:43,271
But second-rate flautists
are 14 for tuppence.

153
00:14:46,320 --> 00:14:48,117
She won't be long.

154
00:14:48,720 --> 00:14:50,676
She make you jealous?

155
00:14:51,160 --> 00:14:54,914
Not much. We've got
so little in common.

156
00:14:55,120 --> 00:14:58,351
She's so pretty.
Cool and detached.

157
00:14:58,560 --> 00:15:02,314
There's nothing messy
about her. I feel like
a brontosaurus when she's about.

158
00:15:02,520 --> 00:15:04,556
A freak survival.
Oh, come off it.

159
00:15:04,760 --> 00:15:08,070
Look, the truth is,
you just missed
being beautiful, George.

160
00:15:08,280 --> 00:15:10,032
Georgina.

161
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:26,675
[SNORING]

162
00:15:31,640 --> 00:15:33,835
Kept the chips warm?
Hey. What?

163
00:15:34,040 --> 00:15:37,271
Kept the chips warm?
George... George threw them away.

164
00:15:37,480 --> 00:15:40,074
MEREDITH:
Well, if you've got something else.

165
00:15:40,720 --> 00:15:42,597
George, what have we...?

166
00:15:43,800 --> 00:15:45,552
Thanks, George.
You're a dear.

167
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:49,392
You must be drunk.
I've had a few vodkas.

168
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:51,279
Does it show?

169
00:15:51,480 --> 00:15:53,232
Got you.
Oh.

170
00:16:12,800 --> 00:16:16,349
[MOANING AND LAUGHING]

171
00:16:23,280 --> 00:16:26,238
It's like an oven in here.
I've got too much on.

172
00:16:33,680 --> 00:16:34,999
I'm off now.

173
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:38,317
Don't leave your flat because of us.
Oh, God, no.

174
00:16:38,520 --> 00:16:41,353
MEREDITH:
Jos, come on.

175
00:16:48,360 --> 00:16:50,920
[***]

176
00:16:59,040 --> 00:17:01,508
[HONKING]

177
00:17:17,240 --> 00:17:19,629
[OPERA MUSIC PLAYS]

178
00:17:38,320 --> 00:17:39,833
Georgy!

179
00:17:41,240 --> 00:17:45,233
Well, if it isn't Georgy Porgy,
visiting the old homestead.

180
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:50,998
How's life in the sink,
Georgy Porgy?

181
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:52,918
Oh, fine, Jimsy Whimsy.

182
00:17:53,280 --> 00:17:55,271
Come in, have a drink.
No, thanks.

183
00:17:55,720 --> 00:17:58,917
Good God, girl,
what have you got on?
A suit of armour, is it?

184
00:17:59,120 --> 00:18:00,712
That's right.
Protects my honour.

185
00:18:00,920 --> 00:18:01,989
[J AMES CHUCKLES]

186
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:05,192
Take it off, for God's sake.
No, I'd rather keep it on, thank you.

187
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:08,995
You've got a decent figure.
Nothing to be ashamed of.
You want to show it off.

188
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:12,033
No, I don't.
Give the boys a treat.

189
00:18:12,560 --> 00:18:14,437
Just look at that thing.

190
00:18:15,360 --> 00:18:18,238
You ought to get a jersey
a couple of sizes smaller.

191
00:18:19,040 --> 00:18:20,632
See?

192
00:18:34,760 --> 00:18:36,239
Right.

193
00:18:38,720 --> 00:18:41,280
Five, ten.
You don't have to pay me.

194
00:18:41,480 --> 00:18:43,118
It's on the house.

195
00:18:43,560 --> 00:18:46,120
It's for a new jumper.
I like this one.

196
00:18:46,320 --> 00:18:47,958
Come on.

197
00:18:49,800 --> 00:18:51,631
Say thank you to Mr James.

198
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:55,514
Thank you, James.
TED: Good girl.

199
00:19:02,240 --> 00:19:03,958
[***]

200
00:20:17,720 --> 00:20:20,996
I don't know.
Dust. Now this.

201
00:20:28,760 --> 00:20:31,069
Praying mantis.
Elephant.

202
00:20:31,280 --> 00:20:32,633
Bloody marvellous.

203
00:20:33,960 --> 00:20:35,871
Ah. Well, thank you, Miss...
Parkin.

204
00:20:36,080 --> 00:20:39,550
Yes. However, just at the moment,
our books seem to be full
of animal imitators.

205
00:20:39,760 --> 00:20:40,715
Oh...

206
00:20:40,920 --> 00:20:43,673
But would you be prepared
to strip, my dear?

207
00:20:43,880 --> 00:20:46,553
Got one or two operation scars.
So much the better.

208
00:20:46,760 --> 00:20:48,716
The customers like that,
within reason, of course.

209
00:20:48,920 --> 00:20:51,753
I have to ask Mummy.
Leave your number. We'll be in touch.

210
00:20:51,960 --> 00:20:54,428
I'll bet you will,
you dirty old slob.

211
00:20:54,640 --> 00:20:56,198
[SIGHS]

212
00:21:02,080 --> 00:21:04,196
We going out?
Why?

213
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:06,470
Aren't you going with Jos or anyone?
No.

214
00:21:07,360 --> 00:21:08,588
Let's go and eat, then.

215
00:21:08,800 --> 00:21:11,678
At the first flicker of dust
and that nonsense,
I'm leaving you.

216
00:21:12,240 --> 00:21:13,434
Trah-la...!

217
00:21:13,640 --> 00:21:15,631
[PHONE RINGING]

218
00:21:15,920 --> 00:21:17,672
[IMITATES MAN]
Parkins' residence.

219
00:21:21,960 --> 00:21:24,599
Hello? Oh, hi.

220
00:21:25,760 --> 00:21:27,193
I might be.

221
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:30,673
[LAUGHING]

222
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:34,955
OK, I'm not doing anything.

223
00:21:35,640 --> 00:21:37,119
Where?

224
00:21:37,840 --> 00:21:39,751
Then you'll have to pick me up.

225
00:21:39,960 --> 00:21:41,871
At the tube in about five minutes.

226
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:44,077
See you.

227
00:21:57,920 --> 00:22:00,832
Where are you going now?
Party. Nick's.

228
00:22:02,080 --> 00:22:04,469
For God's sake, Georgy,
you don't expect me
to have a meal with you

229
00:22:04,680 --> 00:22:06,352
if I can go to a party,
do you?

230
00:22:07,120 --> 00:22:10,317
Look, I didn't mean it like that.
If you'd been the one invited...

231
00:22:10,520 --> 00:22:14,399
I never am.
Don't let's go into that again, Georgy.

232
00:22:16,800 --> 00:22:19,314
OK, if you're gonna be
suicidal, I'll stay.

233
00:22:19,520 --> 00:22:20,794
No, go.

234
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:23,719
Sure?
Sure. Have a lovely time.

235
00:22:23,920 --> 00:22:25,956
I'll think about you
when I drink my cocoa.

236
00:22:28,440 --> 00:22:30,351
Hello.
Bye.

237
00:22:30,600 --> 00:22:32,238
[***]

238
00:22:57,880 --> 00:23:00,599
WOMAN:
Happy birthday, darling.

239
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:04,358
MAN: Many happy returns
of the day, old boy. Glad to see you.

240
00:23:04,560 --> 00:23:06,551
[DOORBELL CHIMES]

241
00:23:08,480 --> 00:23:10,391
Good evening.

242
00:23:12,840 --> 00:23:15,832
What's this, then?
I decided to come.

243
00:23:16,200 --> 00:23:17,792
In this rig-out?

244
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:19,558
You look like a tramp.

245
00:23:19,760 --> 00:23:21,990
Why can't you behave
like a lady, just for once?

246
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:25,272
A lady? OK.

247
00:23:41,600 --> 00:23:43,989
[MUSIC STOPS]

248
00:23:44,240 --> 00:23:45,593
[CROWD CLAPPING]

249
00:23:45,840 --> 00:23:51,198
[GEORGY SINGING
" IT TAKES A WHOLE LOT"]

250
00:23:52,440 --> 00:23:53,759
Come on, boys.

251
00:25:21,760 --> 00:25:23,637
[BAND PLAYING]

252
00:25:30,560 --> 00:25:32,790
[GEORGY LAUGHING
AND SCREAMING]

253
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:34,592
Oh, it's madly gay, darling.

254
00:25:34,800 --> 00:25:36,552
Now, Georgy,

255
00:25:36,760 --> 00:25:40,469
I want you to sit quiet
and listen for a moment.

256
00:25:59,400 --> 00:26:01,072
Georgy,

257
00:26:02,760 --> 00:26:04,398
I'm 49 today.

258
00:26:05,680 --> 00:26:08,069
* For he's a jolly good fellow **
Shut up.

259
00:26:08,280 --> 00:26:10,271
I'm 49.

260
00:26:12,640 --> 00:26:15,200
Notice that, not 50 yet.

261
00:26:16,040 --> 00:26:19,316
When I first met your dad,
I was 27 and just got married.

262
00:26:19,520 --> 00:26:22,318
Your dad was unemployed,
and he couldn't afford
to marry your mother.

263
00:26:22,520 --> 00:26:23,748
I took him on.

264
00:26:23,960 --> 00:26:26,952
She came along as housekeeper,
and they got married.

265
00:26:27,480 --> 00:26:29,710
Ellen and I have never
been blessed with children.

266
00:26:30,120 --> 00:26:34,272
As a result, I've tended to
look upon you as my daughter.

267
00:26:34,480 --> 00:26:37,358
I've always been sorry
that you weren't.

268
00:26:37,560 --> 00:26:38,709
But now I'm glad.

269
00:26:39,240 --> 00:26:41,117
Because of what I did out there?
No. No.

270
00:26:41,320 --> 00:26:43,834
I brought you in here
to make you an offer.

271
00:26:44,040 --> 00:26:46,838
You want to adopt me.
Georgy, please.

272
00:26:47,040 --> 00:26:49,270
No, something quite different.

273
00:26:50,160 --> 00:26:52,355
I want you to be my mistress.

274
00:26:52,560 --> 00:26:54,232
[GLASS CLANGING]

275
00:26:58,240 --> 00:27:00,595
J AMES: I've had it all
drawn up properly.

276
00:27:00,960 --> 00:27:04,430
I propose an agreement whereby
either one of the contracting parties

277
00:27:04,640 --> 00:27:08,394
can opt out at any time
in six months' initial period.

278
00:27:08,640 --> 00:27:14,351
I bear all the expenses
and undertake the formal
adoption of any children.

279
00:27:16,920 --> 00:27:21,471
Here's a copy of the draft contract
for your approval.

280
00:27:26,520 --> 00:27:29,193
I know it all looks pretty formal.

281
00:27:29,480 --> 00:27:33,439
Will we have to have
any shareholders and things?

282
00:27:33,880 --> 00:27:36,997
No, I don't think
that would be necessary.

283
00:27:37,200 --> 00:27:39,873
I should hate to be voted
off the board.

284
00:27:40,760 --> 00:27:43,274
Oh, those annual general meetings.

285
00:27:47,760 --> 00:27:50,877
I hope they'll be
more frequent than that.

286
00:27:51,720 --> 00:27:54,154
I turned up with the Maserati,
and there was this...

287
00:27:56,040 --> 00:27:58,076
Sorry.
WOMAN: What is it?

288
00:27:58,320 --> 00:28:01,073
MAN: Oh, nothing, dear. One of those
vintage Bentleys, all wound up.

289
00:28:01,280 --> 00:28:02,429
J AMES:
Do you mind?

290
00:28:08,920 --> 00:28:10,956
Are you going to say yes or no?
Yes or no.

291
00:28:11,200 --> 00:28:14,397
Don't act the goat, Georgy.
Quite, quite.

292
00:28:15,200 --> 00:28:16,792
Just getting to the small print.

293
00:28:17,000 --> 00:28:19,912
About the alleged condition
of the property...

294
00:28:21,120 --> 00:28:24,157
Does it have to be intact?
Well, it is, isn't it?

295
00:28:24,400 --> 00:28:27,392
Oh, yeah. Queen of all the fairies.
Well, then...

296
00:28:27,600 --> 00:28:29,875
Are there any special conditions
about my duties?

297
00:28:30,600 --> 00:28:32,670
They're understood.
Are they?

298
00:28:33,080 --> 00:28:36,072
I haven't got to wear gymslips
or suck lollipops.

299
00:28:36,320 --> 00:28:38,629
Look, Georgy, if you're not prepared
to discuss this thing seriously...

300
00:28:38,840 --> 00:28:40,558
I mean, what about your wife?

301
00:28:40,760 --> 00:28:42,796
Well, we keep it secret, naturally.

302
00:28:43,000 --> 00:28:45,389
Ellen knows I've done this before.

303
00:28:45,600 --> 00:28:47,352
Oh, I see.

304
00:28:47,560 --> 00:28:49,915
Well, it all seems
quite straightforward.

305
00:28:50,120 --> 00:28:53,192
If there's no other business,
I think we can wind up the meeting.

306
00:29:04,440 --> 00:29:07,512
Oh. Crushed powdered glass
all over the carpet.

307
00:29:52,200 --> 00:29:54,111
My God.

308
00:29:54,720 --> 00:29:56,153
What?

309
00:29:56,360 --> 00:29:58,430
I must be mad.

310
00:29:58,840 --> 00:30:03,709
You're old enough
to be my managing director.

311
00:30:04,400 --> 00:30:05,799
[KNOCKING]

312
00:30:06,000 --> 00:30:07,319
[GLASSES THUDDING]

313
00:30:10,760 --> 00:30:12,716
Come in. Oh.

314
00:30:16,360 --> 00:30:17,588
Oh, pardon me, sir.

315
00:30:17,800 --> 00:30:21,713
Madam said three guests
have arrived, and she
doesn't know them very well.

316
00:30:21,920 --> 00:30:23,717
Yes, right.

317
00:30:24,600 --> 00:30:29,196
Well, you'll let me know
about that offer as soon
as you can, will you?

318
00:30:30,720 --> 00:30:32,233
Oh.

319
00:30:34,360 --> 00:30:35,952
Do you want to see what he offered?

320
00:30:36,160 --> 00:30:38,151
I never pry into anything
Mr James does for you.

321
00:30:38,640 --> 00:30:41,757
I only hope that you know
how to show your gratitude.

322
00:30:43,680 --> 00:30:46,831
[***]

323
00:31:02,400 --> 00:31:04,311
[SPEAKING IN ITALIAN]

324
00:31:04,520 --> 00:31:06,590
[MAN SPEAKING ITALIAN
ON TAPE RECORDER]

325
00:31:11,600 --> 00:31:15,388
What about tonight? I thought
you Eyeties were fast workers.

326
00:31:17,080 --> 00:31:19,548
The Colosseum.
But I want to be alone with you.

327
00:31:19,760 --> 00:31:20,909
Get on with it.

328
00:31:21,120 --> 00:31:22,235
[PHONE RINGING]

329
00:31:22,440 --> 00:31:24,590
[SCREAMS IN ITALIAN]

330
00:31:27,320 --> 00:31:28,435
Meredith's out.
Hell.

331
00:31:28,640 --> 00:31:31,200
But you knew she had a concert.
I forgot.

332
00:31:31,400 --> 00:31:32,799
You got company?

333
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:35,355
Yeah, come and meet him.

334
00:31:39,320 --> 00:31:41,550
<i>My date. My amore.</i>

335
00:31:41,760 --> 00:31:44,069
You must be hard up.
I am. Hadn't you noticed?

336
00:31:44,280 --> 00:31:47,113
Twenty-two, never been kissed.
Pathetic, isn't it?

337
00:31:58,120 --> 00:32:00,190
Let's go.

338
00:32:03,280 --> 00:32:04,713
Come on.
If you're just asking me

339
00:32:04,920 --> 00:32:08,595
because you're sorry for me,
then don't bother. Goodnight.

340
00:32:09,160 --> 00:32:12,948
I know I don't have to bother,
and I'm not sorry for you,
I am asking. So come on!

341
00:32:13,680 --> 00:32:15,398
Wait for us! Hey, come on, Georgy!

342
00:32:15,600 --> 00:32:17,158
Now, this is your big chance.
Don't miss it. Oh.

343
00:32:17,360 --> 00:32:19,237
GEORGY: Oh!
JOS: Oh. Beg your pardon.

344
00:32:19,440 --> 00:32:22,318
[***]

345
00:32:41,320 --> 00:32:43,470
[MUSIC PLAYING]

346
00:33:13,440 --> 00:33:14,509
[CROWD CHATTERING]

347
00:33:14,720 --> 00:33:17,075
[SLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

348
00:34:02,560 --> 00:34:05,233
[JOS WHISTLING]

349
00:35:23,080 --> 00:35:25,594
[GEORGY MOANING]

350
00:35:25,800 --> 00:35:27,313
JOS: Huh?
GEORGY: Jos.

351
00:35:28,480 --> 00:35:30,038
Jos.

352
00:35:32,560 --> 00:35:33,913
Jos!

353
00:35:38,240 --> 00:35:41,596
That's enough of that, George.
Why? I like it!

354
00:35:41,800 --> 00:35:45,998
Why are you stopping?
I know I'm not pretty like Meredith.

355
00:35:46,200 --> 00:35:47,235
[SOBBING]

356
00:35:47,960 --> 00:35:51,589
Oh, God, no!
You're not like Meredith.

357
00:35:51,800 --> 00:35:53,756
I couldn't go to bed with you
like I do her,

358
00:35:53,960 --> 00:35:57,350
then grab a tomato sandwich,
rush out and catch
the 72 bus. Hey.

359
00:36:00,440 --> 00:36:03,955
With you, it would be just
one long, drawn-out,
bloody drama.

360
00:36:04,160 --> 00:36:06,628
All this whining
and carrying on.

361
00:36:07,240 --> 00:36:12,473
You know, the trouble with
you is, you could say
that you're a good girl.

362
00:36:12,680 --> 00:36:14,671
So, I'm sorry, lass.

363
00:36:20,680 --> 00:36:22,398
[DOOR SLAMS]

364
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:25,195
[***]

365
00:36:34,800 --> 00:36:36,472
MEREDITH:
Goodbye, love.

366
00:36:38,680 --> 00:36:40,352
See you.

367
00:36:44,560 --> 00:36:47,393
[CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING]

368
00:37:07,040 --> 00:37:10,715
Have a good time?
So-so.

369
00:37:11,640 --> 00:37:14,393
Didn't lead to bed,
so he can't have been up to much.

370
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:16,513
I want to talk.

371
00:37:16,720 --> 00:37:19,314
Oh. Enough of that.

372
00:37:19,520 --> 00:37:21,078
Oh, Jos!
Oh! Oh!

373
00:37:21,280 --> 00:37:23,635
[JOS GAGS AND CHUCKLES]

374
00:37:23,840 --> 00:37:27,355
I'm bored. Bored living with Georgy.

375
00:37:27,560 --> 00:37:29,152
I think we ought to get married.

376
00:37:29,360 --> 00:37:31,715
We don't fight,
we love it in bed, and...

377
00:37:31,920 --> 00:37:33,558
Well, that's about it, really.

378
00:37:33,760 --> 00:37:35,478
You must be pregnant.

379
00:37:35,680 --> 00:37:37,238
Yes.

380
00:37:43,520 --> 00:37:46,717
Meredith, there's absolutely
no point at all in us getting married
when I know nothing about you

381
00:37:46,920 --> 00:37:49,309
except, well,
things that I don't like.

382
00:37:49,520 --> 00:37:51,351
You take me as me.
Who is you?

383
00:37:51,560 --> 00:37:53,551
Oh, don't give me that rubbish.
I don't ask what you are.

384
00:37:53,760 --> 00:37:55,512
You should if we're gonna
get married and have this kid.

385
00:37:55,720 --> 00:37:59,633
All right, if you're gonna
make this a great big number,
let's pretend I never spoke.

386
00:37:59,880 --> 00:38:02,075
Is it the baby?
What?

387
00:38:02,280 --> 00:38:04,555
That makes you want to marry me?
I just feel like a change.

388
00:38:04,800 --> 00:38:07,268
I can easily get rid of it.
Ha! Just like that?

389
00:38:07,520 --> 00:38:09,590
Why not? I have
no tender feelings about it.

390
00:38:09,800 --> 00:38:11,597
If that's what you wanted,
you shouldn't have told me.

391
00:38:11,800 --> 00:38:13,597
MEREDITH:
Don't be so stupid.

392
00:38:13,840 --> 00:38:15,637
I've destroyed two of yours already.

393
00:38:16,520 --> 00:38:20,274
What? When?
Why didn't you tell me?
Didn't I have a right to know?

394
00:38:20,480 --> 00:38:23,153
Were they my sons
and my daughters?

395
00:38:26,840 --> 00:38:28,990
You won't get rid of this one.
If I want to.

396
00:38:29,200 --> 00:38:30,553
I won't let you.
You can't stop me.

397
00:38:30,760 --> 00:38:34,150
You'll marry me and have it.
Fine. That's what I said at the start.

398
00:38:40,520 --> 00:38:43,717
[LAUGHING]

399
00:39:06,160 --> 00:39:09,152
[GROANING]

400
00:39:17,760 --> 00:39:20,752
You're not. Not again.
Uh.

401
00:39:26,760 --> 00:39:31,117
It's no use you asking me
to lend you the money this time,
because I won't.

402
00:39:31,320 --> 00:39:33,151
I don't care if it's old hat.

403
00:39:33,360 --> 00:39:36,238
I know it's just
a middle-class taboo
and the law needs changing

404
00:39:36,440 --> 00:39:39,159
and the population of these islands
will double by the year 2000.

405
00:39:39,360 --> 00:39:42,352
I won't do it! I'm saving up,
anyway, to go to Majorca.

406
00:39:42,560 --> 00:39:45,028
Oh, shut up, Georgy.
Nobody asked you to.

407
00:39:45,240 --> 00:39:47,196
I'm having this one.

408
00:39:47,400 --> 00:39:50,392
You mean really? Having?
Jos and I are getting married.

409
00:39:50,920 --> 00:39:55,232
No! Darling!
Oh. Georgy, please, you're drooling.

410
00:39:55,440 --> 00:39:58,159
Oh, a baby. That's marvellous.
A baby, a baby!

411
00:39:58,360 --> 00:40:01,830
Don't shout. If I'm gonna
feel like this every morning,
I'll probably change my mind.

412
00:40:02,040 --> 00:40:05,112
Now, you must eat little and often.
Start with a biscuit before you get up.

413
00:40:05,320 --> 00:40:07,072
Don't get out of bed in a hurry.

414
00:40:09,600 --> 00:40:12,592
Don't worry, Meredith.
I'll look after you.

415
00:40:13,680 --> 00:40:17,150
I'm going to be the bridesmaid.
Don't you throw that bouquet at me.

416
00:40:17,400 --> 00:40:20,790
You give it to me carefully
because I won't have
my glasses on. I may drop it.

417
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:22,274
No bridesmaids, darling.

418
00:40:22,480 --> 00:40:25,153
No confetti, organs, vicars,
Mendelssohn or Moss Bros.

419
00:40:25,360 --> 00:40:27,999
Up the registry, quick in and out,
ta very much. Next.

420
00:40:28,200 --> 00:40:30,111
Oh, Meredith,
you must do something.

421
00:40:30,320 --> 00:40:31,799
I'll tell you what, Georgy.
What?

422
00:40:32,000 --> 00:40:34,195
You can be best man.

423
00:40:34,400 --> 00:40:35,355
[GIGGLES]

424
00:40:35,600 --> 00:40:37,477
What about when you're married?
What about it?

425
00:40:37,680 --> 00:40:39,511
You and Jos will be there.
What about me?

426
00:40:39,720 --> 00:40:41,597
Oh. You think you're leaving?
Not if you don't want me to.

427
00:40:41,800 --> 00:40:42,915
I'm easy if you are.

428
00:40:43,120 --> 00:40:45,350
You don't want me to go?
Who'd do the cooking?

429
00:40:45,560 --> 00:40:48,597
Oh, Meredith, I love you.

430
00:40:48,840 --> 00:40:50,512
[***]

431
00:40:51,320 --> 00:40:53,629
Meredith's getting married!
She's pregnant!

432
00:40:54,800 --> 00:40:58,110
That's nice, isn't it?
Typical of the way we're going.

433
00:40:58,320 --> 00:41:01,949
I sometimes wonder to what
the country's coming to.

434
00:41:02,160 --> 00:41:05,550
Don't you go getting yourself
into trouble. That's all!

435
00:41:05,760 --> 00:41:08,433
Doris, don't speak like that.

436
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:11,150
He'd never forgive me.

437
00:41:12,520 --> 00:41:14,238
You've got to drink
your orange juice.
Hasn't she, Jos?

438
00:41:14,440 --> 00:41:17,238
Yes, indeed. Otherwise, this baby
of mine won't have any teeth.

439
00:41:17,440 --> 00:41:19,237
And infant false teeth
can be very expensive.

440
00:41:19,440 --> 00:41:23,558
If your dialogue is this corny now,
Jos Jones, God help us
when we're married.

441
00:41:23,760 --> 00:41:26,399
Oh! Meredith!
Meredith!

442
00:41:26,600 --> 00:41:28,431
At least you take your iron pills.

443
00:41:28,640 --> 00:41:30,551
You see, Mummy dear,
the baby lives
on your blood supply.

444
00:41:30,760 --> 00:41:34,116
Look, I wish you'd both
belt up about this
bloody baby.

445
00:41:34,320 --> 00:41:36,117
I'm off to work.

446
00:41:37,560 --> 00:41:39,357
Don't worry.
The kid will survive.
You know my mother?

447
00:41:39,560 --> 00:41:42,632
Nothing but chips before I was born.
Look at you now, you wreck.

448
00:41:42,840 --> 00:41:45,400
Oh, help. I'm a wreck.
I am. I'm dying.

449
00:41:45,600 --> 00:41:48,751
Yes, my knees are getting weaker,
and there's a flutter in me chest.
There is, a flutter in my chest.

450
00:41:48,960 --> 00:41:51,076
Feel. Oh. Oh. Come here,
come here, come here.

451
00:41:51,280 --> 00:41:53,953
Yes, yes, yes, feel. Ah!

452
00:41:54,160 --> 00:41:56,435
Oh, cor, you ain't half got nice
cold hands, miss.

453
00:41:56,640 --> 00:41:58,949
Yeah, and you'll feel
the wrong side of it
in a minute, my lad.

454
00:41:59,160 --> 00:42:00,559
You wouldn't hit me, miss.

455
00:42:01,360 --> 00:42:02,634
[GROANING]

456
00:42:03,440 --> 00:42:05,158
GEORGY: You and Meredith,
you're hopeless.

457
00:42:05,360 --> 00:42:08,716
If it's the last thing I do,
I'm gonna get you lot organised.

458
00:42:08,920 --> 00:42:10,558
Organised?

459
00:42:19,640 --> 00:42:22,837
And, Miss Perry,
I don't want to
be disturbed.

460
00:42:23,040 --> 00:42:25,429
Very good,
Mr Leamington.

461
00:42:36,400 --> 00:42:39,437
Come over here.
Make yourself comfortable.

462
00:42:40,120 --> 00:42:43,669
Sit down. Go on.

463
00:42:45,240 --> 00:42:48,118
Have you come to give your answer?
Answer?

464
00:42:48,600 --> 00:42:51,637
Oh, no. No, no.
This is serious.

465
00:42:52,320 --> 00:42:55,039
Look, you know you're
always saying that you'll
do anything for me and all that.

466
00:42:55,240 --> 00:42:58,994
Yes.
Well, I need a pram.

467
00:43:02,400 --> 00:43:04,311
And a cot.

468
00:43:05,040 --> 00:43:07,076
And some nappies.

469
00:43:08,440 --> 00:43:11,432
And some blankets
and a highchair and a...

470
00:43:11,640 --> 00:43:13,949
Who is it, Georgy?
Meredith, actually.

471
00:43:14,200 --> 00:43:15,235
Meredith.

472
00:43:17,240 --> 00:43:19,834
But she's a girl.
Yeah, I noticed that too.

473
00:43:20,040 --> 00:43:22,349
That's the sort that usually
has babies, isn't it?

474
00:43:22,880 --> 00:43:25,792
I could wring your neck!

475
00:43:29,600 --> 00:43:31,556
I won't, though.

476
00:43:31,760 --> 00:43:34,752
None of that.
Watch the old blood pressure.

477
00:43:34,960 --> 00:43:37,520
[CHUCKLING]

478
00:43:40,080 --> 00:43:44,039
Can you give me one reason
why I should buy all
that stuff for Meredith?

479
00:43:44,240 --> 00:43:46,674
Well, Meredith
will never bother.

480
00:43:46,880 --> 00:43:48,598
I don't know.

481
00:43:48,800 --> 00:43:51,360
You've got a nerve, you have.

482
00:43:51,560 --> 00:43:55,599
It's what keeps me going, mister.
All right.

483
