with a wife, the husband too.

581
00:53:37,280 --> 00:53:40,511
We share.
You share? Share what? Him?

582
00:53:40,720 --> 00:53:42,472
The flat.

583
00:53:42,680 --> 00:53:44,830
Well, it all seems very offbeat,
if you ask me.

584
00:53:45,040 --> 00:53:46,359
Oh, it is. It's dead kinky.

585
00:53:46,560 --> 00:53:50,553
We all dress up as
Boy Scouts and beat
each other with our woggles.

586
00:53:54,320 --> 00:53:56,436
Get them out of the flat.
I'll pay your rent.

587
00:53:56,640 --> 00:53:58,232
Can't be done.
Why not?

588
00:53:58,440 --> 00:54:00,078
The baby.

589
00:54:00,280 --> 00:54:02,271
Look, I haven't had
my answer yet.

590
00:54:02,480 --> 00:54:03,993
Hey.
Forgot my hat.

591
00:54:04,200 --> 00:54:07,954
Come on. Bye-bye.
Here. Hey.

592
00:54:13,000 --> 00:54:15,230
TED: You know, I won 15 and 6
myself on that race, sir.

593
00:54:15,440 --> 00:54:18,398
What a winner that horse was.
It won't be the last time.

594
00:54:18,600 --> 00:54:21,114
I bet it won't.
The wife's laid
out a buffet supper.

595
00:54:21,320 --> 00:54:23,390
Get us a bottle, Ted.
Right you are, sir.

596
00:54:23,600 --> 00:54:26,831
Nuits-Saint-Georges, perhaps.
That sounds good enough for me, sir.

597
00:54:27,040 --> 00:54:29,395
Doris, Mrs Leamington isn't
joining me for supper, is she?

598
00:54:29,600 --> 00:54:30,999
No, sir.
Right.

599
00:54:31,200 --> 00:54:33,555
Then you'll sit down with me,
won't you, Ted?

600
00:54:33,760 --> 00:54:36,194
Oh. Thank you very much, sir.

601
00:54:36,400 --> 00:54:38,960
Now, that is the end
of a perfect day.

602
00:54:39,160 --> 00:54:40,798
Mr James' horse won.

603
00:54:41,000 --> 00:54:42,831
Mrs Leamington's gone.

604
00:54:43,040 --> 00:54:45,349
Gone?
Gone.

605
00:54:45,560 --> 00:54:47,152
Gone where?

606
00:54:47,880 --> 00:54:48,869
She's dead.

607
00:54:49,080 --> 00:54:52,231
