01:03:30,080 --> 01:03:32,958
Hurry up, my nipples
are freezing.

725
01:03:56,840 --> 01:03:58,319
JOS:
I love you.

726
01:03:58,520 --> 01:04:01,432
I never said that to her
or to anyone.

727
01:04:02,880 --> 01:04:05,348
I've grown to love you
in the right way.

728
01:04:05,560 --> 01:04:09,235
So, that's all right, isn't it?

729
01:04:09,440 --> 01:04:12,273
[***]

730
01:04:31,600 --> 01:04:33,079
Jos?
Huh?

731
01:04:37,240 --> 01:04:40,437
Jos, I love you. I love you.
I know.

732
01:04:41,320 --> 01:04:44,118
It's because I do. It's bec...
Look, don't go on, missus.

733
01:04:44,320 --> 01:04:45,639
It'll be all right.

734
01:04:45,840 --> 01:04:47,796
Will it? Will it?
Shh.

735
01:04:49,480 --> 01:04:52,677
We'll live happily ever after.

736
01:04:54,280 --> 01:04:55,315
[PHONE RINGING]

737
01:04:55,520 --> 01:04:57,590
WOMAN:
Jos! Jos!

738
01:04:57,800 --> 01:04:58,755
[KNOCKING]

739
01:04:58,960 --> 01:05:00,154
Jos!

740
01:05:01,160 --> 01:05:02,593
JOS: What is it?
WOMAN: It's Peg.

741
01:05:02,840 --> 01:05:04,831
JOS: Eh? Peg? Oh, that's short
for Margaret, isn't it?

742
01:05:05,040 --> 01:05:07,634
Yes. Well, look, I can't
invite you in, you see,
I've just got out of bed.

743
01:05:07,840 --> 01:05:09,956
Jos. Don't you want to know
about Meredith?

744
01:05:10,160 --> 01:05:11,798
What? She's asleep.

745
01:05:12,000 --> 01:05:13,592
Is she?

746
01:05:13,800 --> 01:05:15,472
I've just come back
from the hospital.

747
01:05:15,680 --> 01:05:17,511
She's started her pains.

748
01:05:19,520 --> 01:05:22,034
Oh.
What's going on?

749
01:05:22,240 --> 01:05:24,993
Why weren't you here?
I'll write you a letter, dear.

750
01:05:26,240 --> 01:05:29,312
PEG: Are you alone?
Belt up, Peg. Is there anything else?

751
01:05:29,520 --> 01:05:33,229
No. The nurses said
I couldn't be much help,
and you're to ring at 8.

752
01:05:33,440 --> 01:05:36,830
There we are, then. Ring at 8.
Jos, we're going to the hospital.

753
01:05:37,040 --> 01:05:38,917
Yea, but look, Peg says
we don't have to go till tomorrow.

754
01:05:39,120 --> 01:05:41,554
She's having your baby! Yours!

755
01:05:42,160 --> 01:05:45,038
[GASPING]

756
01:05:51,400 --> 01:05:56,428
Naughty. We don't need
the gas and air till we get
much stronger contractions.

757
01:05:56,640 --> 01:05:59,393
Have you ever had a baby?
No, but I've brought in hundreds.

758
01:05:59,600 --> 01:06:01,477
Then belt up and leave me
alone with this.

759
01:06:01,680 --> 01:06:03,875
You speak to me like that,
I'll take it away all together.

760
01:06:05,640 --> 01:06:06,868
There's a visitor for you.

761
01:06:08,560 --> 01:06:10,357
All right, dear.

762
01:06:22,360 --> 01:06:25,432
That's right.
Try to get some bye-byes.

763
01:06:25,640 --> 01:06:27,312
I'll bring you a couple of aspirin.

764
01:06:28,120 --> 01:06:31,351
It's like burning,
and she says aspirin.

765
01:06:31,560 --> 01:06:33,471
Oh, Meredith.

766
01:06:33,680 --> 01:06:35,477
Spiritual experience.

767
01:06:35,680 --> 01:06:37,477
[LAUGHING]

768
01:06:37,680 --> 01:06:39,511
Ow.

769
01:06:42,600 --> 01:06:45,353
[CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

770
01:06:47,120 --> 01:06:48,394
[GROANING]

771
01:06:49,200 --> 01:06:50,599
JOS:
Help.

772
01:06:51,760 --> 01:06:53,159
Thank you, my dear.

773
01:06:53,360 --> 01:06:57,035
What is your name
and your telephone number?

774
01:06:57,240 --> 01:06:59,913
Thank you. Goodbye.
Goodbye.

775
01:07:11,120 --> 01:07:12,075
MEREDITH:
Georgy.

776
01:07:12,360 --> 01:07:16,148
[SOBBING]

777
01:07:43,400 --> 01:07:45,436
[YAWNS]

778
01:07:47,720 --> 01:07:49,631
[SNIFFING]

779
01:07:51,000 --> 01:07:53,116
[GROANING]

780
01:07:56,080 --> 01:07:58,116
Hey, what time is it?
Half past 8.

781
01:07:58,320 --> 01:08:00,151
Oh, I'd better ring.

782
01:08:00,840 --> 01:08:06,278
A girl. Seven pounds, two ounces.
Born at 6.30. Both doing well.

783
01:08:06,640 --> 01:08:08,392
Oh, you rang.
That's what they said?

784
01:08:13,160 --> 01:08:14,388
Seven pounds, two ounces.

785
01:08:14,600 --> 01:08:17,194
Hey, that's not bad
for someone her size.

786
01:08:17,400 --> 01:08:18,992
A girl.

787
01:08:19,520 --> 01:08:23,195
Hey, that's better, in a way.
A boy needs more from a father.

788
01:08:24,040 --> 01:08:26,076
What name did we choose
for it if it's a girl?

789
01:08:26,280 --> 01:08:27,508
Sara, without an H.

790
01:08:27,720 --> 01:08:30,837
Sara, Sara, Sara, Sara, Sara.

791
01:08:31,440 --> 01:08:34,477
Sara? Eh? Sara.

792
01:08:34,680 --> 01:08:38,116
Sounds like some international
combine or club or something.

793
01:08:38,320 --> 01:08:42,518
Society for the Admiration
of Risky Anecdotes.

794
01:08:45,080 --> 01:08:47,275
Well, shall we drink
to babby's health? Eh?

795
01:08:47,480 --> 01:08:50,074
Hey, throw me in a piece
of fried bread, would you?

796
01:08:52,920 --> 01:08:54,558
Sara.

797
01:08:55,080 --> 01:08:56,957
Long life and happiness.
Yes.

798
01:08:57,160 --> 01:08:59,754
Good luck, mate.
You'll need it,
with her for a mother.

799
01:08:59,960 --> 01:09:02,520
Amazing things happen to women
when they have children.

800
01:09:02,720 --> 01:09:05,473
The most unexpected people
suddenly turn out natural mothers.

801
01:09:05,680 --> 01:09:07,557
I don't know why she didn't
get rid of it.

802
01:09:07,760 --> 01:09:10,194
She went through hell to have it.
She deserved to.

803
01:09:10,400 --> 01:09:11,753
No one deserves to.

804
01:09:11,960 --> 01:09:13,552
She was in agony,
and she needed us.

805
01:09:13,760 --> 01:09:15,751
We were in there
rolling about on the floor.

806
01:09:15,960 --> 01:09:17,791
Well, we didn't know.

807
01:09:18,280 --> 01:09:20,032
Give me another.

808
01:09:21,600 --> 01:09:23,272
Bad luck, your first time.

809
01:09:23,480 --> 01:09:25,232
It's the absolute story of my life.

810
01:09:25,440 --> 01:09:27,715
No matter what I try,

811
01:09:28,560 --> 01:09:30,949
God's always got a custard pie
up his sleeve.

812
01:09:31,160 --> 01:09:34,470
Very good, Miss Parkin.
I'm afraid most of the pathetic clowns
are cast this season.

813
01:09:34,680 --> 01:09:37,353
Oh. Give it a rest, Jos.
Hey.

814
01:09:37,560 --> 01:09:39,596
Are you interested in small parts?

815
01:09:39,800 --> 01:09:41,518
I know most girls aren't these days,

816
01:09:41,720 --> 01:09:44,871
but, you know, you seem
to have had such bad luck
in this direction.

817
01:09:46,800 --> 01:09:48,518
I love you.

818
01:09:49,400 --> 01:09:51,470
I love you.

819
01:10:00,960 --> 01:10:02,188
[GARGLING]

820
01:10:02,400 --> 01:10:04,550
God, isn't it marvellous
without her?

821
01:10:04,760 --> 01:10:07,149
Don't say that.
Oh, sorry.

822
01:10:07,360 --> 01:10:08,873
Say the first thing that comes
into your head.

823
01:10:09,080 --> 01:10:10,354
Yes, it is. Oh.

824
01:10:12,600 --> 01:10:14,955
Time I got dressed.

825
01:10:16,240 --> 01:10:17,832
Oh, blimey.

826
01:10:18,040 --> 01:10:20,508
Hey, do you think
you could make the bedroom?

827
01:10:20,720 --> 01:10:23,393
No.
Well, I'll try.

828
01:10:25,080 --> 01:10:27,275
[***]

829
01:10:33,280 --> 01:10:35,874
Here we are. That's the wrong room.
Put me down.

830
01:10:36,080 --> 01:10:37,149
JOS: What?
GEORGY: Oh.

831
01:10:37,360 --> 01:10:40,397
Oh! Oh!
Oh, Jos, please put me down.

832
01:10:40,600 --> 01:10:44,070
Jos, please put me down.
Jos, please. Would you please...?

833
01:11:05,960 --> 01:11:09,475
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

834
01:11:22,320 --> 01:11:25,039
MAN: How long?
Doctor said eight weeks.

835
01:11:28,480 --> 01:11:31,472
Hi.
Where have you been?

836
01:11:48,080 --> 01:11:49,559
How are you feeling?

837
01:11:49,760 --> 01:11:51,398
Lousy.

838
01:11:57,080 --> 01:11:59,275
Well? Aren't you going
to look at it?

839
01:11:59,480 --> 01:12:03,598
This is your marvellous child
you couldn't bear being
destroyed, remember?

840
01:12:07,000 --> 01:12:09,389
It's hideous. I hate it.

841
01:12:10,720 --> 01:12:12,870
It gave me hell.

842
01:12:15,160 --> 01:12:17,390
All new babies look like that.

843
01:12:17,600 --> 01:12:19,989
You'll like it when it's a bit older.
Oh, no.

844
01:12:20,200 --> 01:12:21,758
I want it adopted. Now.

845
01:12:36,080 --> 01:12:38,833
I've got a rotten headache.
Have you got any aspirin
or dope or anything?

846
01:12:39,040 --> 01:12:41,270
Not that I couldn't use myself.

847
01:12:42,000 --> 01:12:43,956
How do you set about
adoption anyway?

848
01:12:44,160 --> 01:12:47,630
If I ask the nurses here,
they'll plague me with sermons.

849
01:12:51,800 --> 01:12:53,392
You're a bitch.

850
01:12:53,600 --> 01:12:54,999
You're a bastard.

851
01:12:55,280 --> 01:12:57,748
[***]

852
01:13:06,800 --> 01:13:08,279
How is she?

853
01:13:08,480 --> 01:13:10,072
Fine.

854
01:13:10,280 --> 01:13:13,955
Wanna go up and see her?
No, can't.

855
01:13:14,160 --> 01:13:15,832
Well, come on, then.

856
01:13:17,120 --> 01:13:19,475
Is she proud of the baby?
Yes, yes.

857
01:13:19,680 --> 01:13:22,069
Keeps drooling over it all the time.
I told you so.

858
01:13:22,280 --> 01:13:24,714
JOS: It's a bit strange, really,
because she's dead ugly.

859
01:13:24,920 --> 01:13:25,909
Sara?

860
01:13:26,120 --> 01:13:28,953
JOS: She's got cauliflower ear,
a terrible squint.

861
01:13:29,160 --> 01:13:31,310
GEORGY: That poor baby.
Horrible wig-join. You can see it

862
01:13:31,520 --> 01:13:33,590
from one end of the ward to the other.
Jos!

863
01:13:33,800 --> 01:13:36,439
Hey, look.
That's not funny!

864
01:13:36,640 --> 01:13:37,595
JOS:
Catch me!

865
01:13:54,640 --> 01:13:58,189
[BABY CR YING]

866
01:14:19,000 --> 01:14:20,956
That's why adoption
is so tricky to arrange.

867
01:14:21,160 --> 01:14:23,628
You can't be sure the mother
knows her own mind.

868
01:14:23,840 --> 01:14:27,628
Oh, don't worry. You can
be sure in this case.
I think it's probably the only way.

869
01:14:27,840 --> 01:14:30,832
The home situation is a bit offbeat.
Offbeat? How do you mean?

870
01:14:31,040 --> 01:14:31,995
[KNOCKING]

871
01:14:32,200 --> 01:14:33,519
Excuse me.

872
01:14:33,880 --> 01:14:37,190
Sister, shall I take her to the nursery?
Oh, no. Just hold on a minute.

873
01:14:37,400 --> 01:14:40,517
I was discussing her with Mr Jones...
Hey, George.

874
01:14:43,880 --> 01:14:46,110
Jos. How are you?

875
01:14:46,320 --> 01:14:49,232
Congratulations!
You said you weren't coming.

876
01:14:49,480 --> 01:14:50,833
I've changed my mind.

877
01:14:51,040 --> 01:14:52,553
I'm so thrilled about the baby.

878
01:14:52,760 --> 01:14:54,557
Oh, are you visiting Mrs Jones?

879
01:14:54,800 --> 01:14:57,268
Yes. I'm her sister,
Georgina Jones.
I've been out of the country.

880
01:14:57,480 --> 01:14:58,549
I couldn't get in sooner.

881
01:14:58,800 --> 01:15:01,189
Surely Jones is her married name.

882
01:15:01,800 --> 01:15:02,994
Yes.

883
01:15:03,200 --> 01:15:06,795
Well, I mean,
her sister-in-law.
I'm Jos' sister.

884
01:15:07,000 --> 01:15:08,479
That's my baby.

885
01:15:08,920 --> 01:15:10,751
GEORGY: Can I hold her?
JOS: Sure.

886
01:15:10,960 --> 01:15:13,520
Have a hold. Be my guest.

887
01:15:23,760 --> 01:15:25,478
Jos.

888
01:15:26,480 --> 01:15:28,118
Oh, Jos.

889
01:15:30,680 --> 01:15:32,432
Meredith, you're
looking marvellous.

890
01:15:33,640 --> 01:15:35,437
Where have you been?

891
01:15:36,360 --> 01:15:37,759
GEORGY: I've just seen her.
MEREDITH: Who?

892
01:15:38,000 --> 01:15:40,116
Sara.
Oh, that.

893
01:15:40,320 --> 01:15:42,834
Honestly, she's going to be
a real knockout,
just like her mother.

894
01:15:43,040 --> 01:15:45,554
Look, Georgy, please,
none of the hearts-and-flowers
mother-Iove bit.

895
01:15:45,760 --> 01:15:48,228
No, honestly, she's beautiful.
She's just like you.

896
01:15:48,480 --> 01:15:50,755
Shut up, Georgy, will you?
Oh, come on, Meredith.

897
01:15:50,960 --> 01:15:54,430
You're feeling down in the dumps.
Don't you tell me what I'm feeling.

898
01:15:56,280 --> 01:15:58,635
As far as I'm concerned,
when I leave this hospital,
I leave alone.

899
01:15:58,840 --> 01:16:01,673
All very sad and that, but...
GEORGY: Don't talk like that, Meredith.

900
01:16:01,920 --> 01:16:04,593
I'm not having my life cluttered
with some screeching baby.

901
01:16:04,840 --> 01:16:06,558
The flat's all ready,
and I'm leaving.

902
01:16:06,760 --> 01:16:09,797
It wouldn't be fair to have me
hanging around the three of you.

903
01:16:10,000 --> 01:16:12,798
What have you been telling her?
What?

904
01:16:13,800 --> 01:16:16,189
Well, whatever it is,
just get this straight, Georgy:

905
01:16:16,400 --> 01:16:18,789
I'm having this baby adopted,
and that's that.

906
01:16:24,920 --> 01:16:28,037
You're not. You're not going
to give Sara away.

907
01:16:28,240 --> 01:16:30,390
Not now you've seen
and touched her.

908
01:16:30,600 --> 01:16:32,033
I don't touch her.
I leave it to them.

909
01:16:32,240 --> 01:16:34,037
Now, just a minute, young lady.

910
01:16:34,280 --> 01:16:36,589
You stay out of it, you old bag.
You can't.

911
01:16:36,800 --> 01:16:39,473
How can you not want to hold her
and take care of her?

912
01:16:39,680 --> 01:16:41,272
God, the embarrassment.

913
01:16:41,480 --> 01:16:44,233
OK. If you're so keen
on this bloody thing,
then you have it.

914
01:16:44,440 --> 01:16:47,910
Free, gratis and for nothing.
With none of the attendant pain
or discomfort.

915
01:16:48,160 --> 01:16:51,516
Instant families!
Yes, all right. I will.

916
01:16:51,720 --> 01:16:53,039
Of course I will.

917
01:16:53,240 --> 01:16:55,674
I wouldn't wish
a mother like you on her!

918
01:16:55,920 --> 01:16:58,309
You're a cow, Meredith!

919
01:16:58,840 --> 01:17:02,833
It's all right, everybody.
Keep calm. Nothing whatever
to do with you.

920
01:17:03,040 --> 01:17:04,553
Yes.

921
01:17:05,200 --> 01:17:06,428
Well.

922
01:17:17,840 --> 01:17:20,149
Get rid of all this junk, Ted.
Yes.

923
01:17:20,360 --> 01:17:22,191
Dispose of all the sad reminders, sir.

924
01:17:22,400 --> 01:17:25,278
Of course, of course.

925
01:17:27,880 --> 01:17:29,154
Come on, Jos.
JOS: I'm coming.

926
01:17:29,360 --> 01:17:32,352
Come on, quick. Come on.

927
01:17:32,560 --> 01:17:34,949
I'm not used to this.
You're holding her wrong.

928
01:17:35,160 --> 01:17:36,593
What do you mean?

929
01:17:38,000 --> 01:17:40,309
That's better.
Now, you make the tea.

930
01:17:40,520 --> 01:17:44,229
Oh, baby. Oh, baby.

931
01:17:44,560 --> 01:17:46,676
[***]

932
01:17:55,480 --> 01:17:56,549
MAN:
Darling.

933
01:17:56,760 --> 01:17:57,795
[HONKING]

934
01:18:18,640 --> 01:18:21,313
They can start reading
at 18 months
if the letters are big.

935
01:18:21,520 --> 01:18:22,839
She'll start before that.

936
01:18:23,040 --> 01:18:24,837
JOS: Bank sensation.
You're late.

937
01:18:25,080 --> 01:18:27,833
The books were out 5 pence.
It was every man for himself.

938
01:18:28,080 --> 01:18:30,355
You two trying to lose weight?
It's like a pressure cooker.

939
01:18:30,760 --> 01:18:33,513
The nappies have to be done.
We don't want nappy rash, do we?

940
01:18:33,840 --> 01:18:35,114
No, we don't.

941
01:18:35,320 --> 01:18:36,833
How's the basket?
Getting on.

942
01:18:37,080 --> 01:18:38,433
I meant this one.

943
01:18:38,720 --> 01:18:41,188
Goochy. Goochy. Goochy.

944
01:18:41,520 --> 01:18:43,556
So much for fatherhood.

945
01:18:44,200 --> 01:18:46,509
What's this one for?
Catching heads?

946
01:18:46,720 --> 01:18:48,517
Oh, Jos.
Did you get paid?

947
01:18:48,720 --> 01:18:51,314
Wealth, wealth, wealth,
beyond the dreams of avarice.

948
01:18:51,520 --> 01:18:52,839
Hey, let's go the pictures, Georgy.

949
01:18:53,040 --> 01:18:55,076
Oh, we can't, Jos,
because we can't leave Sara.

950
01:18:55,280 --> 01:18:56,872
Peg will look after her,
won't you, my old beauty?

951
01:18:57,120 --> 01:18:59,156
GEORGY: No, she can't, Jos.
Sorry, my pottery class.

952
01:19:01,760 --> 01:19:03,352
Damn.

953
01:19:03,560 --> 01:19:06,358
Well, you go by yourself.
Oh, that's fun.

954
01:19:06,560 --> 01:19:09,120
Well, I've got masses to do.
I don't mind, honestly.

955
01:19:09,320 --> 01:19:10,639
Are you sure?

956
01:19:10,840 --> 01:19:14,515
Absolutely.
Whoopee.

957
01:19:16,120 --> 01:19:18,680
I'll have to get me skates on.

958
01:19:25,280 --> 01:19:27,077
J AMES:
Do you get it?

959
01:19:27,280 --> 01:19:29,874
Yes. Yes, I see.
Do you really?

960
01:19:30,080 --> 01:19:34,073
What I mean is lace,
soft and white, like...

961
01:19:34,280 --> 01:19:37,795
Like lace. You know, lots of...

962
01:19:38,000 --> 01:19:39,194
Lace.

963
01:19:39,400 --> 01:19:41,436
Right. All over.

964
01:19:41,640 --> 01:19:45,633
All over. Yes, well,
if you're quite sure.

965
01:19:45,840 --> 01:19:48,308
